infection control, as applicable to the infection: 

1. Staff education and infection surveillance; 

2. Interruption of transmission of microorganisms by eradicating infecting; microorganisms from their epidemiologically
important reservoirs, and/or preventing person-to-person transmission; and

3. Modifying host risk for infection. 

